I really like the concept here, but the execution is incredibly standard and doesn't do the concept justice. It's a diary entry that tells you the events in the plainest possible manner, leaves nothing to the imagination, and makes the story ultimately feel rather flat. There's very little emotion present in the article because it feels rushed and doesn't take care with the characterisation and the emotions of the character. Meanwhile, the diary entry just tells the reader the story instead of showing it to them, which is a real shame because this concept presents some great opportunities to let the reader discover what's going on for themselves. It's the perfect setup for a short article that implies what's going on but doesn't state it outright, but instead, this just tells you everything straight up in standard fashion. -1







